reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 13, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It is a bit roomy with this "thin" itx board
reviews.reviewText: It is bit spacious with this thin itx board, it has a built-in 19v power plug. I installed only 1 low profile Noctua CPU fan and the Core Temp hoovered around the high 40+ C for a i5-12400. The added on items are: 1 CPU, 1 fan, 1TB M.2 2280 drive, 1 AX210 Wifi 6, pair of DDR4 RAM, and a 120W, 19V, 6.32A external power supply. Be careful that the motherboard is thin so don't over tighten the CPU fan screws to bend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome thin ITX setup for really small build.
reviews.reviewText: Although I did not buy it from here on Amazon. I've been patiently waiting for this board as I had spare 32GB set of laptop ram, wifi card and M.2 NVME laying around. Just had to pick up a CPU and I went with an i5 12400 for this setup. After receiving this board I had installed all the components inside a nice small case. Since I had an Dell Alienware laptop, I figured that the power supply would just fit in there. However I was surely mistaken. So after a few attempts, I finally figured what type of power supply was require as the manual only states a 19v DC power supply.So to save you guys some time in searching for a power supply. You will need a 5.5mm barrel connector power supply. Just search Asus Rog Laptop Charger, 19.5V 9.23A 180W Asus Power Adapter and this will work perfectly for this mobo. Originally I used a Dell 7.5mm barrel connector and that didn't work. Was so frustrated that I then I bought a 4.5mm barrel connector style power supply and still did not work. Had I known this info prior then it would had saved me a lot of time. Just order the Asus power supply and save yourself the headache. Hopefully this will help someone.Overall I love the layout of the board. With the most current 12th Gen Intel chip and Intel AX201 wifi it is hard to beat. Do not exceed 65W CPU though.
